Package: sudo-considered-harmful
Provides: prevent-sudo
Depends: ${misc:Depends}
Architecture: all
XB-Important: yes
Conflicts: calife,
           doas,
           gosu,
           libsss-sudo,
           pleaser,
           sudo,
           sudo-ldap,
           super
Description: Prevent installation of sudo and similar tools
 sudo has a history of security issues allowing privilege escalation
 despite its main goal is to restrict escalated
 privilege. Additionally it is not wise to just guard root permissions
 with the same password as a normal user logs in.
 .
 This package prevents the installation of sudo, super, doas, calife,
 and similar tools.
